('104', '483', '8 Best Modems for Comcast Xfinity in 2021', '8-best-modems-for-comcast-xfinity-in-2021', '<header class=\"entry-header\">\n<h1 class=\"entry-title\"> </h1>\n</header>\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\n<p>As a Comcast Xfinity subscriber, you must be spending $14-20/month for internet equipment lease. It looks like a small amount in the beginning, but by the end of the year, you shall end up paying around $168-230, which is more than enough to own a high-end modem and use it for more than 3-4 years (or even more.)</p>\n<p>However, you can’t pick a random modem and connect it and if you’ve <a href=\"https://approvedmodems.org/modem-buying-guide/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">decided to buy a modem</a>, then you will have to get a Xfinity compatible modem. Not only that, you’ll also need to make sure that the device you’re getting is capable of handling the service package speeds you’ve subscribed to.</p>\n<p>You could <a href=\"https://www.xfinity.com/support/devices/\" rel=\"nofollow external\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">go through their official list</a>, which has all the compatible modems that they’ve approved. However, it includes <a href=\"https://approvedmodems.org/bad-modems/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">many bad quality modems</a>, which can create serious internet usage issues. That’s why being a networking professional, I decided to use popular modems suited for the different service package.</p>\n<p>After weeks of testing over 37 modems from different brands, including Arris, Motorola, Netgear, etc., I’m here with the list of Xfinity recommended modems that provide a reliable internet experience, have no latency issues, come with no security vulnerabilities, and are highly suitable with the different service packages.</p>\n<p>Note: It’s not just Comcast, almost all the providers such as <a href=\"https://approvedmodems.org/spectrum/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">Spectrum</a>, <a href=\"https://approvedmodems.org/sparklight/\" data-wpel-link=