tps://untigering.com/unschooling-as-an-asian-american-is-an-act-of-resistance/</a></p>\n<p>Vegan Homeschooling:<a href=\"http://veganhomeschool.com/\"> http://veganhomeschool.com/</a> </p>\n<p>Grandparent Homeschooling:<a href=\"https://homeeducator.com/homeschooling-grandchildren/\"> https://homeeducator.com/homeschooling-grandchildren/</a> </p>\n<p>Charter Schools: <a href=\"http://www.homefires.com/charter/\"> http://www.homefires.com/charter/</a></p>\n<p>Easy Peasy: Free, on-line, all grades:  <a href=\"https://allinonehomeschool.com/\">https://allinonehomeschool.com/</a></p>\n<p>Teaching Textbooks: Math 3 to Pre-Calculus:  <a href=\"http://www.teachingtextbooks.com/\">http://www.teachingtextbooks.com/</a></p>\n<p>Ambleside Online:  Weekly schedules, free, all grades: <a href=\"https://amblesideonline.org/\">https://amblesideonline.org/</a></p>\n<p>Bob Jones University Press Homeschool info:<a href=\"https://www.homeworksbyprecept.com/\"> https://www.homeworksbyprecept.com/</a></p>\n<p>Math U See:<a href=\"https://www.mathusee.com/\"> https://www.mathusee.com/</a></p>\n<p>K12: <a href=\"https://www.k12.com/\">https://www.k12.com/</a> Government Sponsored, Mandated Vaccines required </p>\n<p>Valor Global Online: https://valoronline.org/</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://tuttletwins.com/email/as-more-parents-decide-to-permanently-homeschool-were-helping-make-it-easier-and-more-affordable/?mc_cid=59902efeb8&amp;mc_eid=7120603c25%3C/%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ehttps://tuttletwins.com/email/as-more-parents-decide-to-permanently-homeschool-were-helping-make-it-easier-and-more-affordable/?mc_cid=59902efeb8&amp;mc_eid=7120603c25%3C/%3E%3C/a%3E%3C/p%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href=\">https://fee.org/articles/back-to-school-no-thanks-say-millions-of-new-homeschooling-parents/?utm_source=email&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=2020_FEEWeekly</a></p>\n<p>Homeschooling 101 article:<br /><a href=\"https://www.thehomeschoolmom.com/homeschooling-101/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.thehomeschoolmom.com/homeschooling-101/</a></p>\n<p>Sources of free homeschool curricula: <a href=\"https://freedomhomeschooling.com/free-christian-homeschool-curriculum/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://freedomhomeschooling.com/free-christian-homeschool-curriculum/</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.thoughtco.com/free-homeschool-resources-4151635\">https://www.thoughtco.com/free-homeschool-resources-4151635</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://howdoihomeschool.com/2019/11/06/free-homeschooling-curriculum-packages/\">https://howdoihomeschool.com/2019/11/06/free-homeschooling-curriculum-packages/</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.successful-homeschooling.com/free-homeschooling-curriculum.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">http://www.successful-homeschooling.com/free-homeschooling-curriculum.html</a></p>\n<p>Whole homeschooling curricula: <a href=\"https://www.robinsoncurriculum.com/rc/homeschool-curriculum-excellence/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.robinsoncurriculum.com/rc/homeschool-curriculum-excellence/</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ronpaulcurriculum.com/\">https://www.ronpaulcurriculum.com</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.calverteducation.com/\">https://www.calverteducation.com/</a></p>\n<p>Christian curricula: <a href=\"https://www.aop.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.aop.com</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.abeka.com/Homeschool/\">https://www.abeka.com/Homeschool/</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.sonlight.com/\">https://www.sonlight.com</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.christianbook.com/page/homeschool/\">https://www.christianbook.com/page/homeschool/</a></p>\n<p>Sources for either whole curricula and/or supplements: <a href=\"https://www.rainbowresource.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.rainbowresource.com</a></p>\n<p>Source for a variety of homeschool curricula that serve various styles of learning and educational supplements. They have homeschooling consultants available. <a href=\"https://www.lovetolearn.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.lovetolearn.net</a></p>\n<p>Curriculum, homeschooling helps and enrichments. Unschoolers may find resources here as well. <a href=\"https://www.christianbook.com/page/homeschool?navcat=Homeschool\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.christianbook.com/page/homeschool?navcat=Homeschool</a></p>\n<p>Christian Book Distributors publishes their own homeschooling catalog and has been a major provider of Christian curricula for years. <a href=\"https://iew.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://iew.com</a></p>\n<p>Institute for Excellence in Writing – a source of reading, spelling, grammar and writing resources from K-12. Video training for teachers and students. Highly recommended, especially for reluctant writers. <a href=\"https://www.aop.com/horizons.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.aop.com/horizons.html</a></p>\n<p>Publisher of Horizons math and phonics curricula, thorough and easy to use programs. Colleges: <a href=\"https://www.hillsdale.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.hillsdale.edu</a></p>\n<p>Hillsdale College has free enrichment courses on the Constitution, Economics, History, etc. For teens and adults. <a href=\"https://www.phc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.phc.edu</a> Patrick Henry College offers challenging dual enrollment courses for students over 16. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.loveandlogic.com/products/schooling-at-home-webinar\">https://www.loveandlogic.com/products/schooling-at-home-webinar</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.masterbooks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Masterbooks Where Faith Grows </a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.masterbooks.com/apologetics\">Masterbooks Apologetics</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.masterbooks.com/creation\">Masterbooks Creation</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.masterbooks.com/homeschool-curriculum\">Masterbooks Homeschooling</a></p>\n<p>Be sure to join through <a href=\"http://www.ronpaulhomeschool.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">http://www.RonPaulHomeschool.com</a>, a special link that gives $160 in free bonuses, including a signed, personalized copy of my New York Times bestseller The Politically Incorrect Guide to American History.  </p>\n<p>The Good and The Beautiful <a href=\"https://www.goodandbeautiful.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.goodandbeautiful.com/</a></p>\n<p>Christian, Self-paced, Online Homeschooling Courses with Customizable Curriculum: <a href=\"https://schoolhouseteachers.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://schoolhouseteachers.com/</a></p>\n<p>Logic and Faith in the context of Jon Rappoport’s Logic and Analysis Course: <a href=\"https://nomorefakenews.com/logiccourseoutline.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://nomorefakenews.com/logiccourseoutline.html</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.publicschoolexit.com/\">https://www.publicschoolexit.com/</a></p>\n<p>13 Reasons to Unschool: <a href=\"https://www.unschooling.com/t/13-reasons-why-not-to-go-to-school/298/2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.unschooling.com/t/13-reasons-why-not-to-go-to-school/298/2</a></p>', '1', '115', '2021-09-03 22:36:47', '82', '', '2021-11-10 10:10:59', '82', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2021-09-03 22:36:47', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"spfeatured_image\":\"images\\/2021\\/10\\/31\\/challenges-of-homeschooling.png\",\"spfeatured_image_alt\":\"\",\"post_format\":\"standard\",\"gallery\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"video\":\"\",\"link_title\":\"\",\"link_url\":\"\",\"quote_text\":\"\",\"quote_author\":\"\",\"post_status\":\"\"}', '16', '1', '', '', '1', '63', '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', '1', '*', '', ''),
('111', '490', 'Connecting your Laravel project to MySQL database', 'connecting-your-laravel-project-to-mysql-database', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">Connecting your laravel project to MySQL database is moderately easy. Since we have done the installation with XAMPP. It comes along with already installed MySQL and PHPMyAdmin.</p>\r\n', '\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">In this tutorial, I will make use of phpMyAdmin to create a new database that will connect to the laravel application. This post is assuming you already have a laravel project setup in your local and you are able to access its homepage via localhost or custom set domain name.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important; font-weight: bold;\"><u style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\">Step1: Create a new database via phpmyadmin</u></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">Navigate to domain name.dev/ PHPMyAdmin, Click on the Databases tab and create a new database with your wanted name.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">Clicking on create will create a new database in your XAMPP MySQL.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\"><u style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important; font-weight: bold;\">Step2: Changes in.env configuration file</span></u></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">Once the database is created, you need to tell your laravel project the details about the database.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">Laravel 5 has a pretty simple way to do that, All configuration that you should stay private and should not share goes into the .env file of your laravel project.</p>\r\n<pre style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; overflow: auto; font-family: \'Operator Mono\', \'Fira Code\', Consolas, Monaco, \'Andale Mono\', monospace; font-size: 12px; padding: 10px; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px; line-height: 2; color: #000000; word-break: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; background: rgba(238, 238, 238, 0.35); border: none; border-radius: 3px; text-shadow: #ffffff 0px 1px; direction: ltr; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.125) 0px 1px 1px; outline: none !important;\">DB_CONNECTION=mysql<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\" />DB_HOST=190.0.0.1<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\" />DB_PORT=4008<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\" />DB_DATABASE=testProject<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\" />DB_USERNAME=root<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\" />DB_PASSWORD=</pre>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">Modify the following property in your .env file according to your database settings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important; font-weight: bold;\"><u style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\">Step3: Run migration (optional)</u></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">To test if you\'ve got with success combined your Laravel project to the database you\'ll run the migration command. Laravel project by default comes with some default table for storing users and their password request. once you run migrate command you it ought to produce the default tables for you within the database.</p>\r\n<pre style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; overflow: auto; font-family: \'Operator Mono\', \'Fira Code\', Consolas, Monaco, \'Andale Mono\', monospace; font-size: 12px; padding: 10px; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px; line-height: 2; color: #000000; word-break: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; background: rgba(238, 238, 238, 0.35); border: none; border-radius: 3px; text-shadow: #ffffff 0px 1px; direction: ltr; tab-size: 4; hyphens: none; position: relative; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.125) 0px 1px 1px; outline: none !important;\">php artisan migrate</pre>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">That’s it! You are now ready to make database operations in your project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 25px; color: #676767; font-family: Camphor, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; outline: none !important;\">Source: <a href=\"https://lavalite.org/blog/connecting-your-laravel-project-to-mysql-database\">https://lavalite.org/blog/connecting-your-laravel-project-to-mysql-database</a> </p>', '1', '117', '2021-10-28 07:34:04', '82', '', '2021-11-11 15:11:02', '82', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2021-10-28 07:34:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"spfeatured_image\":\"images\\/2021\\/11\\/11\\/connecting-your-laravel-project-to-mysql-database.jpg\",\"spfeatured_image_alt\":\"\",\"post_format\":\"standard\",\"gallery\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"video\":\"\",\"link_title\":\"\",\"link_url\":\"\",\"quote_text\":\"\",\"quote_author\":\"\",\"post_status\":\"\"}', '5', '0', '', '', '1', '26', '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', '0', '*', '', ''),
('112', '491', 'Apache Reverse Proxy: Content From Different Websites', 'apache-reverse-proxy-content-from-different-websites', '<section class=\"dh di dj dk dl\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"n p\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dm ai aj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; min-width: 0px; width: 680px; max-width: 680px; margin: 0px 64px;\">\r\n<p id=\"3ae8\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">In this tutorial let us discuss how to include content from different websites into the main website through Reverse Proxy</p>\r\n<h2 id=\"8716\" class=\"ig ih dp bp ii ij ik il im in io ip iq ir is it iu iv iw ix iy iz ja jb jc jd em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 1.72em 0px -0.31em; font-family: sohne, \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #292929; line-height: 28px; letter-spacing: 0px; font-size: 22px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Reverse Proxy</h2>\r\n<p id=\"7a60\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl je hn ho hp jf hr hs ht jg hv hw hx jh hz ia ib ji id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.86em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">A<span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\"> proxy server</span> is an intermediary server that forwards requests for content from multiple clients to different servers across the Internet.</p>\r\n<p id=\"7973\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">A <span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">reverse proxy server</span> is a type of proxy server that typically sits behind the firewall in a private network and directs client requests to the appropriate backend server. A reverse proxy provides an additional level of abstraction and control to ensure the smooth flow of network traffic between clients and servers.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"nm nn no np nq nr ct cu paragraph-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 56px auto 0px; clear: both;\">\r\n<div class=\"ns nt es nu aj nv\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 680px; position: relative; cursor: zoom-in; z-index: auto; transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.2, 1) 0s;\" tabindex=\"0\">\r\n<div class=\"ct cu nl\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1283px;\">\r\n<div class=\"nz s es oa\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: relative; margin: auto; background-color: #f2f2f2;\">\r\n<div class=\"ob oc s\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding-bottom: 383.703px; height: 0px;\">\r\n<div class=\"js nw t u v jn aj au nx ny\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; overflow: hidden; height: 383.703px; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 100ms ease 400ms; will-change: transform; transform: translateZ(0px);\"><img class=\"t u v jn aj od oe kj wx\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 383.703px; visibility: hidden; filter: blur(20px); transform: scale(1.1); transition: visibility 0ms ease 400ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/30/1*v4Pp0pG5WMbknprejifVmw.png?q=20\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"395\" /></div>\r\n<img class=\"ka ww t u v jn aj c\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 383.703px; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 400ms ease 0ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*v4Pp0pG5WMbknprejifVmw.png\" sizes=\"700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/276/1*v4Pp0pG5WMbknprejifVmw.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*v4Pp0pG5WMbknprejifVmw.png 552w, https://miro.medium.com/max/640/1*v4Pp0pG5WMbknprejifVmw.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*v4Pp0pG5WMbknprejifVmw.png 700w\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"395\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"ff9a\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Common uses for a reverse proxy server include:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none;\">\r\n<li id=\"903b\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if of og oh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; margin-bottom: -0.46em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 30px; padding-left: 0px; font-size: 21px; margin-top: 2em;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">Load balancing</span> — A reverse proxy server can act as a load balancer in front of your backend servers and distribute the client requests across a group of servers.</li>\r\n<li id=\"beb9\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl oi hn ho hp oj hr hs ht ok hv hw hx ol hz ia ib om id ie if of og oh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; margin-bottom: -0.46em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 30px; padding-left: 0px; font-size: 21px; margin-top: 1.05em;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">Web acceleration</span> — Reverse proxies can compress inbound and outbound data, as well as cache commonly requested content, both of which speed up the flow of traffic between clients and servers. They can also perform additional tasks such as SSL encryption to take a load off of your web servers, thereby boosting their performance.</li>\r\n<li id=\"451e\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl oi hn ho hp oj hr hs ht ok hv hw hx ol hz ia ib om id ie if of og oh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; margin-bottom: -0.46em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 30px; padding-left: 0px; font-size: 21px; margin-top: 1.05em;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">Security and anonymity</span> — By intercepting requests headed for your backend servers, a reverse proxy server protects their identities and acts as an additional defense against security attacks. It also ensures that multiple servers can be accessed from a single URL.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<div class=\"n p en on oo op\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 14px; padding-top: 24px; padding-bottom: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: medium;\"> </div>\r\n<section class=\"dh di dj dk dl\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"n p\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dm ai aj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; min-width: 0px; width: 680px; max-width: 680px; margin: 0px 64px;\">\r\n<h2 id=\"83b3\" class=\"ig ih dp bp ii ij ik il im in io ip iq ir is it iu iv iw ix iy iz ja jb jc jd em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 1.72em 0px -0.31em; font-family: sohne, \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #292929; line-height: 28px; letter-spacing: 0px; font-size: 22px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Apache Reverse Proxy</h2>\r\n<p id=\"c80d\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl je hn ho hp jf hr hs ht jg hv hw hx jh hz ia ib ji id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.86em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Apache httpd(as well as most other web servers) can act as a reverse proxy server, also-known-as a “gateway” server.</p>\r\n<p id=\"34f1\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">In this case, httpd itself does not generate or host the data, but rather the content is obtained by one or several backend servers, which normally have no direct connection to the external network.</p>\r\n<p id=\"f31d\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">The httpd receives a request from a client, the request itself is <em class=\"kt\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">proxied</em> to one of these backend servers, which then handles the request, generates the content, and then sends this content back to httpd, which then generates the actual HTTP response back to the client.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"nm nn no np nq nr ct cu paragraph-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 56px auto 0px; clear: both;\">\r\n<div class=\"ns nt es nu aj nv\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 680px; position: relative; cursor: zoom-in; z-index: auto; transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.2, 1) 0s;\" tabindex=\"0\">\r\n<div class=\"ct cu nl\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1283px;\"><img class=\"aj ou ov\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; width: 680px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*vPgcWpdshV6ut3Nz3izmzg.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"395\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"238f\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">The mod_proxy is the Apache module helps us to configure the Reverse Proxy to the different backend servers, mod_proxy is not an individual module but a collection of them</p>\r\n<p id=\"1331\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy</span> — the main Apache module for proxying connections; it allows Apache to act as a gateway to the underlying application servers.</p>\r\n<p id=\"13fb\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy_http </span>— which adds support for proxying HTTP connections.</p>\r\n<p id=\"43af\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy_balancer</span> — which adds load balancing features for multiple backend servers.</p>\r\n<p id=\"3cc9\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy_ftp — </span>which adds support for proxying FTP connections</p>\r\n<p id=\"0556\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy_connect — </span>which adds support for SSL tunneling</p>\r\n<p id=\"d6ca\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy_ajp</span> <span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">— </span>which adds support for AJP protocol</p>\r\n<p id=\"9421\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy_html — </span>Rewrite HTML links in to ensure they are addressable from Clients’ networks in a proxy context.</p>\r\n<p id=\"5eda\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">mod_proxy_http2 — </span>which adds support for HTTP/2 protocol</p>\r\n<p id=\"4319\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Let us see how to include content from the different backend server to send the response back to the client.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<div class=\"n p en on oo op\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 14px; padding-top: 24px; padding-bottom: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: medium;\"> </div>\r\n<section class=\"dh di dj dk dl\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"n p\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dm ai aj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; min-width: 0px; width: 680px; max-width: 680px; margin: 0px 64px;\">\r\n<h2 id=\"935e\" class=\"ig ih dp bp ii ij ik il im in io ip iq ir is it iu iv iw ix iy iz ja jb jc jd em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 1.72em 0px -0.31em; font-family: sohne, \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #292929; line-height: 28px; letter-spacing: 0px; font-size: 22px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Reverse Proxy to include content from different backend:</h2>\r\n<p id=\"4ec7\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl je hn ho hp jf hr hs ht jg hv hw hx jh hz ia ib ji id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.86em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">The Reverse proxy can be used to include the content from the different backend servers/websites and exposed to the client through a single Domain.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"nm nn no np nq nr ct cu paragraph-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 56px auto 0px; clear: both;\">\r\n<div class=\"ns nt es nu aj nv\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 680px; position: relative; cursor: zoom-in; z-index: auto; transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.2, 1) 0s;\" tabindex=\"0\">\r\n<div class=\"ct cu nl\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1283px;\"><img class=\"aj ou ov\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; width: 680px; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*NSP05hfjPSQAHlZhNoM3Gw.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"395\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"4e38\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Here we are using the proxy_http to reverse proxy the request to different back end server/websites based on the request path, the other proxy modules can be used based on your uses cases(proxy_http module helps to connect any URL’s enabled through http/https).</p>\r\n<p id=\"e3af\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">End-user access the domain myexample.com, Apache Reverse Proxy server sending the request to different backend servers(<span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">proxied to different websites</span>) based on the request context root. The end-user will not see the back end server details, the internal links will be changed to myexample.com so that the end-user will see only myexample.com also all the content will be requested through the same myexample.com domain.</p>\r\n<ul class=\"\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none;\">\r\n<li id=\"9d4d\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if of og oh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; margin-bottom: -0.46em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 30px; padding-left: 0px; font-size: 21px; margin-top: 2em;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">If the user accesses any subresources from/test1, the reverse proxy internally fetches the resource from Backend Server 1 and responds the data to the end-user, before responding to the proxy server rewrite the internal links.</li>\r\n<li id=\"9694\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl oi hn ho hp oj hr hs ht ok hv hw hx ol hz ia ib om id ie if of og oh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; margin-bottom: -0.46em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 30px; padding-left: 0px; font-size: 21px; margin-top: 1.05em;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">If the user access any subresources from/test2, the reverse proxy internally fetches the resource from Backend Server 2 and responds the data to the end-user, before responding to the proxy server rewrite the internal links.</li>\r\n<li id=\"3701\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl oi hn ho hp oj hr hs ht ok hv hw hx ol hz ia ib om id ie if of og oh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; margin-bottom: -0.46em; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 30px; padding-left: 0px; font-size: 21px; margin-top: 1.05em;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">If the user accesses any other resources, the reverse proxy internally fetches the resource from Backend Server 3 and responds the data to the end-user, before responding to the proxy server rewrites the internal links.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<div class=\"n p en on oo op\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 14px; padding-top: 24px; padding-bottom: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: medium;\"> </div>\r\n<section class=\"dh di dj dk dl\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div class=\"n p\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dm ai aj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; min-width: 0px; width: 680px; max-width: 680px; margin: 0px 64px;\">\r\n<h2 id=\"94f1\" class=\"ig ih dp bp ii ij ik il im in io ip iq ir is it iu iv iw ix iy iz ja jb jc jd em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 1.72em 0px -0.31em; font-family: sohne, \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #292929; line-height: 28px; letter-spacing: 0px; font-size: 22px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Reverse Proxy Configurations in Apache:</h2>\r\n<p id=\"8b44\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl je hn ho hp jf hr hs ht jg hv hw hx jh hz ia ib ji id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.86em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Enable the mod_proxy, mod_proxy_http and modules in httpd.conf</p>\r\n<pre class=\"nm nn no np nq ow go be\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 56px; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-x: auto; background: #f2f2f2; padding: 20px;\"><span id=\"c867\" class=\"em ig ih dp ox b kv oy oz s pa\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: block; color: #292929; line-height: 1.18; letter-spacing: -0.022em; font-size: 16px; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, \'Courier New\', Courier, monospace; margin-top: -0.09em; margin-bottom: -0.09em; white-space: pre-wrap;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">LoadModule proxy_module modules/mod_proxy.so<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\" />LoadModule proxy_http_module modules/mod_proxy_http.so<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\" />LoadModule proxy_html_module modules/mod_proxy_html.so</span></pre>\r\n<p id=\"2a95\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Enable the Virtualhost with the required Proxy configurations and Server Name(domain for accessing the website Apache Reverse Proxy: Content From Different website)— replace localhost:&lt;port number&gt; with the actual back end server URL or the website URL.</p>\r\n<pre style=\"color: #000000; overflow-wrap: break-word; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /><br />&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;\r\n    ServerAdmin webmaster@dummy-host.example.com\r\n    DocumentRoot \"c:/Apache24/docs/myexample.com\"\r\n    ServerName myexample.com\r\n    ErrorLog \"logs/myexample.com-error.log\"\r\n    CustomLog \"logs/myexample.com-access.log\" common \r\n \r\n     ProxyHTMLEnable On\r\n \r\n     ProxyPassMatch    \"/test1/(.*)\" \"http://localhost:8080/$1\"\r\n     ProxyPassReverse  \"/test1/\" \"http://localhost:8080/\"\r\n\r\n     ProxyPassMatch    \"/test2/(.*)\" \"http://localhost:8081/$1\"\r\n     ProxyPassReverse  \"/test2/\" \"http://localhost:8081\"\r\n\r\n     ProxyPassMatch    \"/(.*)\" \"http://localhost:8082/$1\"\r\n     ProxyPassReverse  \"/\" \"http://localhost:8082/\"\r\n\r\n     &lt;Location \"/test1/\"&gt;\r\n      ProxyHTMLURLMap / /test1/\r\n     &lt;/Location&gt; \r\n\r\n     &lt;Location \"/test2/\"&gt; \r\n      ProxyHTMLURLMap / /test2/\r\n     &lt;/Location&gt; \r\n \r\n&lt;/VirtualHost&gt; </pre>\r\n<p id=\"4376\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">ProxyHTMLEnable — </span>A simple switch to enable or disable the proxy_html filter, the proxy_html module provides an output filter to rewrite HTML links in a proxy situation, to ensure that links work for users outside the proxy</p>\r\n<p id=\"0ef5\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">ProxyPassMatch — </span>This directive allows remote servers to be mapped into the space of the local server, makes use of regular expressions instead of a simple prefix matching</p>\r\n<p id=\"d318\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">ProxyPassReverse — </span>This directive lets Apache httpd adjust the URL in the <code class=\"oa pc pd pe ox b\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: #f2f2f2; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, \'Courier New\', Courier, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15.75px;\">Location</code>, <code class=\"oa pc pd pe ox b\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: #f2f2f2; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, \'Courier New\', Courier, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15.75px;\">Content-Location</code> and <code class=\"oa pc pd pe ox b\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-color: #f2f2f2; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, \'Courier New\', Courier, monospace; padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15.75px;\">URI</code> headers on HTTP redirect responses to the incoming server name</p>\r\n<p id=\"97fb\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">ProxyHTMLURLMap — </span>This is the key directive for rewriting HTML links. When parsing a document, whenever a link target matches from-pattern, the matching portion will be rewritten to to-pattern(this helps to resolve the subsequent requests through the Reverse Proxy)</p>\r\n<p id=\"df50\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Now while accessing <a class=\"bv ls\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit; text-decoration-line: underline; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://myexample.com/test1/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://myexample.com/test1/</a>, the request is internally reverse proxied to the backend server1(8080)</p>\r\n<p id=\"78c5\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">The internal CSS links and other links are rewritten</p>\r\n<figure class=\"nm nn no np nq nr ct cu paragraph-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 56px auto 0px; clear: both;\">\r\n<div class=\"ns nt es nu aj nv\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 680px; position: relative; cursor: zoom-in; z-index: auto; transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.2, 1) 0s;\" tabindex=\"0\">\r\n<div class=\"ct cu pf\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px;\">\r\n<div class=\"nz s es oa\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: relative; margin: auto; background-color: #f2f2f2;\">\r\n<div class=\"pg oc s\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; height: 0px; padding-bottom: 382.734px;\">\r\n<div class=\"js nw t u v jn aj au nx ny\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; overflow: hidden; height: 382.734px; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 100ms ease 400ms; will-change: transform; transform: translateZ(0px);\"><img class=\"t u v jn aj od oe kj wx\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 382.734px; visibility: hidden; filter: blur(20px); transform: scale(1.1); transition: visibility 0ms ease 400ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/30/1*_kGkZ-ZP8O5j9FxUNcOWrQ.png?q=20\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" /></div>\r\n<img class=\"ka ww t u v jn aj c\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 382.734px; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 400ms ease 0ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*_kGkZ-ZP8O5j9FxUNcOWrQ.png\" sizes=\"700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/276/1*_kGkZ-ZP8O5j9FxUNcOWrQ.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*_kGkZ-ZP8O5j9FxUNcOWrQ.png 552w, https://miro.medium.com/max/640/1*_kGkZ-ZP8O5j9FxUNcOWrQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*_kGkZ-ZP8O5j9FxUNcOWrQ.png 700w\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"ff74\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">While accessing <a class=\"bv ls\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit; text-decoration-line: underline; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://myexample.com/test2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://myexample.com/test2</a>, the request is internally reverse proxied to the backend server2(8081)</p>\r\n<p id=\"975c\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">The internal CSS links and other links are rewritten</p>\r\n<figure class=\"nm nn no np nq nr ct cu paragraph-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 56px auto 0px; clear: both;\">\r\n<div class=\"ns nt es nu aj nv\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 680px; position: relative; cursor: zoom-in; z-index: auto; transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.2, 1) 0s;\" tabindex=\"0\">\r\n<div class=\"ct cu pf\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px;\">\r\n<div class=\"nz s es oa\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: relative; margin: auto; background-color: #f2f2f2;\">\r\n<div class=\"pg oc s\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; height: 0px; padding-bottom: 382.734px;\">\r\n<div class=\"js nw t u v jn aj au nx ny\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; overflow: hidden; height: 382.734px; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 100ms ease 400ms; will-change: transform; transform: translateZ(0px);\"><img class=\"t u v jn aj od oe kj wx\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 382.734px; visibility: hidden; filter: blur(20px); transform: scale(1.1); transition: visibility 0ms ease 400ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/30/1*zp2YlXrUWa1fwGwMYfpqUw.png?q=20\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" /></div>\r\n<img class=\"ka ww t u v jn aj c\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 382.734px; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 400ms ease 0ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*zp2YlXrUWa1fwGwMYfpqUw.png\" sizes=\"700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/276/1*zp2YlXrUWa1fwGwMYfpqUw.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*zp2YlXrUWa1fwGwMYfpqUw.png 552w, https://miro.medium.com/max/640/1*zp2YlXrUWa1fwGwMYfpqUw.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*zp2YlXrUWa1fwGwMYfpqUw.png 700w\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"7938\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">While accessing <a class=\"bv ls\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: inherit; text-decoration-line: underline; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://myexample.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://myexample.com</a> (any URL that not starts with /test1 or /test2), the request is internally reverse proxied to the backend server3(8082)</p>\r\n<p id=\"a699\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">The internal CSS links and other links are rewritten</p>\r\n<figure class=\"nm nn no np nq nr ct cu paragraph-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 56px auto 0px; clear: both;\">\r\n<div class=\"ns nt es nu aj nv\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; width: 680px; position: relative; cursor: zoom-in; z-index: auto; transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.2, 1) 0s;\" tabindex=\"0\">\r\n<div class=\"ct cu pf\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px;\">\r\n<div class=\"nz s es oa\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: relative; margin: auto; background-color: #f2f2f2;\">\r\n<div class=\"pg oc s\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; height: 0px; padding-bottom: 382.734px;\">\r\n<div class=\"js nw t u v jn aj au nx ny\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; overflow: hidden; height: 382.734px; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 100ms ease 400ms; will-change: transform; transform: translateZ(0px);\"><img class=\"t u v jn aj od oe kj wx\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 382.734px; visibility: hidden; filter: blur(20px); transform: scale(1.1); transition: visibility 0ms ease 400ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/30/1*vM2OmSkOonDllgC0mfpCPA.png?q=20\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" /></div>\r\n<img class=\"ka ww t u v jn aj c\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 680px; height: 382.734px; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 400ms ease 0ms;\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*vM2OmSkOonDllgC0mfpCPA.png\" sizes=\"700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/276/1*vM2OmSkOonDllgC0mfpCPA.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*vM2OmSkOonDllgC0mfpCPA.png 552w, https://miro.medium.com/max/640/1*vM2OmSkOonDllgC0mfpCPA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*vM2OmSkOonDllgC0mfpCPA.png 700w\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"fb2b\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Users always access the external domain(myexample.com) but the content is internally reverse proxied from different backend servers or websites.</p>\r\n<p id=\"a731\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Some additional Proxy related configurations</p>\r\n<p id=\"d255\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">SSLProxyEngine — </span>This directive toggles the usage of the SSL/TLS Protocol Engine to connect to the backend proxy.</p>\r\n<p id=\"652d\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">ProxyPassReverseCookieDomain — </span>Adjusts the Domain string in Set-Cookie headers from a reverse- proxied server</p>\r\n<p id=\"5642\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">ProxyPassReverseCookiePath — </span>Adjusts the Path string in Set-Cookie headers from a reverse- proxied server</p>\r\n<p id=\"881f\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\"><span class=\"hk jj\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bold;\">ProxyPreserveHost — </span>Use incoming Host HTTP request header for proxy request</p>\r\n<p id=\"f06c\" class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">This Reverse Proxy will help in multiple scenarios, display content from different sites(back end server) through a single domain to the end-user. This approach can be used while migrating the websites from one platform to another platform, the legacy platform can host some of the content paths through Reverse Proxy until the platform is completely migrated to the new platform.</p>\r\n<p class=\"hi hj dp hk b hl hm hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if dh em\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word; color: #292929; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: charter, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px;\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\">Source:  <a href=\"https://medium.com/swlh/apache-reverse-proxy-content-from-different-websites-3e82df87a34a\">https://medium.com/swlh/apache-reverse-proxy-content-from-different-websites-3e82df87a34a</a> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', '', '1', '120', '2021-10-28 07:34:04', '82', '', '2021-11-11 15:18:07', '82', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2021-10-28 07:34:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"spfeatured_image\":\"images\\/2021\\/11\\/11\\/reverse-proxy.png\",\"spfeatured_image_alt\":\"\",\"post_format\":\"standard\",\"gallery\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"video\":\"\",\"link_title\":\"\",\"link_url\":\"\",\"quote_text\":\"\",\"quote_author\":\"\",\"post_status\":\"\"}', '5', '0', '', '', '1', '30', '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', '0', '*', '', '');/**ABDB**/
